==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''*leuþo-'', from Indo-European ''*lěu-, *lǎu-''.

Cognate with Old High German [[liod]] (German [[Lied]]), Old Saxon [[lioð]] (Dutch [[lied]]), Old Norse ''ljōð'' ‘verse, song’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /le:oθ/

===Noun===
'''lēoþ''' ''n'' (''pl'' '''lēoþ''')
# a [[song]]

